@startuml name "Deki JSON command loop sequence"
title "Deki Slice 2 - bounded JSON command loop sequence"
rightfooter Runtime sequence for issue #675; no app-data approvals or streaming UI in this slice

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 24
skinparam BoxPadding 12

actor User
participant "DekiSurface\nsrc/features/shell/deki" as UI
participant "runDetachedDekiSend\nsrc/features/shell/deki/lib" as Send
participant "runDekiEntry\nsrc/engine/deki" as Entry
participant "dekiApi.prompt\nsrc/shared/api" as Api
participant "Tauri/remote invoke\nshared/api + http_dispatch" as Invoke
participant "deki_prompt\nsrc-tauri commands/storage/deki.rs" as Runtime
participant "Prompt builder\ndeki/prompt.rs" as Prompt
participant "Loop coordinator\ndeki/loop.rs" as Loop
participant "Model client\ndeki/model_client.rs" as ModelClient
participant "Protocol parser\ndeki/protocol.rs" as Protocol
participant "Evidence budgeter\ndeki/budget.rs" as Budget
participant "Typed command registry\ndeki/commands/mod.rs" as Commands
participant "LLM provider\nsrc-tauri/crates/llm" as Llm
database "AppState.storage" as Storage
collections "Repo root\nbounded source files" as Repo
participant "Public web\napproved grants only" as Web
participant "Action parser\ndeki/action_parser.rs" as ActionParser

User -> UI : send prompt
UI -> Send : runDetachedDekiSend(input)
Send -> Send : persist user message\ncompact history if needed
Send -> Entry : runDekiEntry(request, dekiApi)
Entry -> Api : prompt(DekiEntryRequest)
Api -> Invoke : invoke "deki_prompt"
Invoke -> Runtime : deki_prompt(state, request)

Runtime -> Runtime : resolve connection\nvalidate request and session context
Runtime -> Prompt : build system + task prompt\ninclude approved chat/web grants\ninclude JSON protocol instructions
Prompt --> Runtime : prompt parts + initial context
Runtime -> Loop : run bounded JSON command loop
Loop -> Budget : initialize named limits\nrounds=8, commands/round=4,\nwall time=90s, evidence caps
Loop -> ModelClient : chat request with plain messages\nno native tool calls
ModelClient -> Llm : De-Koi Rust LLM transport
Llm --> ModelClient : assistant text
ModelClient --> Loop : assistant JSON frame or final text
Loop -> Protocol : extract exactly one command frame

alt valid command frame with stop=false
    Protocol --> Loop : say + typed commands + stop=false
    loop bounded rounds until stop, timeout, abort, or max rounds
        Loop -> Budget : check round, wall-time,\ncommand-count, trace budgets
        alt budget available
            Loop -> Commands : execute typed read-only commands
            alt repo read/search/list
                Commands -> Repo : read/search bounded safe paths
                Repo --> Commands : bounded result
            else Deki library read
                Commands -> Storage : list/get allowed creative-library data
                Storage --> Commands : bounded overview/detail result
            else approved chat read
                Commands -> Storage : read only granted chat/message window
                Storage --> Commands : bounded chat result
            else approved web search/page read
                Commands -> Web : exact granted query or allowed URL\nbounded results/pages/time
                Web --> Commands : bounded public source text
            else unsupported or mutating command
                Commands --> Loop : structured error result
            end
            Commands --> Budget : raw command result
            Budget --> Loop : compact evidence + trace item\nwith truncation notes
            Loop -> ModelClient : next turn with hidden bounded evidence
            ModelClient -> Llm : plain chat completion
            Llm --> ModelClient : assistant text
            ModelClient --> Loop : next JSON frame
            Loop -> Protocol : parse/strip frame
        else budget, timeout, or abort exhausted
            Budget --> Loop : controlled stop reason
        end
    end
else final frame or stop=true
    Protocol --> Loop : visible say/message/final + stop=true
else ambiguous/multiple/malformed frame
    Protocol --> Loop : deterministic protocol error
end

Loop --> Runtime : visible assistant text,\nread-only trace summary,\ncontrolled stop reason if any
Runtime -> ActionParser : parse optional <deki_action>\nfrom final visible text only
ActionParser --> Runtime : cleaned visible content + action
Runtime --> Invoke : { content, createdAt, action }
Invoke --> Api : DekiGatewayResponse
Api --> Entry : response
Entry -> Entry : normalizeDekiEntryAction
Entry --> Send : DekiEntryResponse
Send -> UI : persist assistant message
UI --> User : render final answer + existing action card

note right of Protocol
  JSON control frames are never saved to Deki history.
  Fenced JSON can be tolerated only when stripped from visible output.
  Protocol parsing must not inspect inside <deki_action> blocks.
end note

note right of Commands
  Slice 2 commands are read-only and typed.
  Web search/page reads are included only after a matching grant.
  Dry-run mutation plans and approval resolution are Slice 3.
end note

note right of Budget
  Every command result is compacted before model feedback.
  Truncation must be explicit and include how to narrow the next command.
end note

note right of Runtime
  Existing <deki_action> behavior remains the bridge to current UI approvals
  until Slice 4 adds streamed tool and approval events.
end note

@enduml
